track_notes:
There is a small parking area (2-3 vehicles) at the start of the Jackrabbit ski trial. The first half of the hike is along the Jackrabbit trail and is an easy trip. Turn right at the intersection to head for the summit.

The trail gets progressively worse and the last half mile is rough, rocky and about 1000 of elevation gain. It gets better from there, you have a two small summits to traverse before you get to McKenzie.

The summit is very wooded and difficult to erect a dipole.

There are some views along the way and from spots on the summit. Unfortunately our trip was blanketed in fog and mist the entire time.
